This paper belongs to the field of natural language processing and information retrieval, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as it covers topics related to natural language processing, including text summarization. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper deals with collecting corpora for automatic summarization, which is a key task in information retrieval. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper mentions using state-of-the-art summarization systems, which are often based on machine learning techniques. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with automated summarization, which is a common task in AI research. 

cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely sub-category, but it is possible as the paper discusses the use of live blogs in online journalism, which has implications for the societal impact of technology.
